Hi Zach,

I refer to my Privacy Act 2020 requests for full copies of the claim =
files for C90306048 and C90306256, including all internal notes, =
reports, third-party correspondence, scopes, assessments, emails, phone =
records, texts, and any other relevant materials.

Despite my request of 1 July 2025, and my reminder to Grant on 27 August =
2025, I have not yet received any material. Your reference to a 25 July =
2025 email or communications is unclear, so could you kindly resend that =
correspondence so I have a complete record. Please provide the full =
claim files by 5:00 pm, Monday 1 September 2025, as the 20-working-day =
timeframe under the Privacy Act has already passed.

For ongoing compliance, I would also appreciate monthly updates, =
provided on the 1st of each month, of the full and up-to-date files. If =
providing full copies each month is difficult, then per Information =
Privacy Principle 6, I am happy to receive monthly summaries of all new =
additions, with the complete file supplied whenever an assessment is =
submitted or presented.

In relation to the contents claim, to date I have only received a =
partial list from David, which does not include item values, repair or =
cleaning details, or assessment of property outside the house, including =
under-deck stairs and deck items, many of which were significantly =
affected by heat and smoke. As more than three months have now passed =
without a complete schedule or proper assessment, I would be grateful =
for an urgent update on this claim.

In relation to the house claim, I look forward to receiving the =
comprehensive update from Grant as he indicated. As per his request, I =
am also happy to meet on site, and I can make myself available on: =
Monday at 4:00 pm, (Tuesday at either 8:00 am or 4:00 pm, Wednesday =
after 3:30 pm, or Thursday before 3:00 pm. Please confirm whichever =
option works best.

While progress to date has been slower than anticipated, I trust that =
the matters will now move forward in a timely way consistent with the =
Code=E2=80=99s requirements.

Kind regards,
Raffaella


> On 28 Aug 2025, at 10:18=E2=80=AFAM, Claims <Claims@tower.co.nz> =
wrote:
>=20
